{"type":"message","id":"279dfa68","parentId":"c99987a0","timestamp":"2026-03-29T15:31:56.142Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-03-29 11:31 EDT] [Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/1). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\n\n[Subagent Task]: Fix the BillsWidget, MoneyWidget, and HabitsWidget in the Mission Control React app at /Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/\n\nThese widgets exist but don't fetch data. Fix them to load from and save to the API server.\n\nThe API server is running on localhost:3001. The Vite dev server proxies /api/* to it (via vite.config.ts).\n\n**IMPORTANT: Use relative URLs like `/api/bills` — these go through the Vite proxy.**\n\nThe API endpoints (already built in server/mission-control-api.cjs):\n- GET /api/bills → {bills: [{id, name, amount, dueDate, category, paid}]}\n- POST /api/bills/action → {action: \"add\"|\"delete\"|\"markPaid\", bill: {id, name, amount, dueDate, category}}\n- GET /api/money → {money: [{id, date, description, amount, type}]}\n- POST /api/money/action → {action: \"add\"|\"delete\", item: {...}}\n- GET /api/habits → {habits: [{id, name, color, completedDates: [\"2026-03-29\"]}]}\n- POST /api/habits/action → {action: \"add\"|\"delete\"|\"toggle\", habit: {id}, date: \"2026-03-29\"}\n\nFor each widget, add:\n1. useState for loading (like RemindersWidget)\n2. useEffect that fetches data on mount\n3. Add/delete/mark-complete actions that POST to the API and update state\n4. Loading skeleton while fetching\n5. DO NOT set loading=false on every fetch — only on initial load\n\nBillsWidget: add useEffect (mount only), fetch GET /api/bills, show bills list. Add \"Add Bill\" button, delete button, markPaid button.\nMoneyWidget: add useEffect (mount only), fetch GET /api/money, show income/expense list.\nHabitsWidget: add useEffect (mount only), fetch GET /api/habits, show habits with toggle for today.\n\nKeep the existing frosted glass iOS 26 styling. Don't change the visual design — just add the data logic.\n\nMake sure hasLoaded ref is used so loading only goes false after first successful fetch.\n\nAfter fixing, test: curl -s http://localhost:3001/api/bills should return {bills:[]} (empty is fine, but the widget should render without crashing).\n\nOutput: Fix the 3 widget files in /Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/src/components/"}],"timestamp":1774798316139}}
